INSTALLATION
============

1) If you are on the Aciss cluster, run the installation script:
      ./install_aciss


2) ENVIRONMENT SETUP:

To set up the MATLABYRINTH environment variable in bash: 
  export MATLABYRINTH=/home11/ozog/sand/MATLAByrinth

Then add MATLAByrinth to your path:
  export PATH=$PATH:$MATLABYRINTH/bin

If it does not already exist, create a Matlab startup file:
  mkdir -p ~/Documents/MATLAB
  vi ~/Documents/MATLAB/startup.m

and append these lines to the startup.m file:
  % MATLABYRINTH:
  if isempty( getenv( 'MATLABYRINTH' ) ) 
  	display('Please set the MATLABYRINTH environment variable' );
  else
  	addpath( [getenv( 'MATLABYRINTH' ) , 'src/matlab'] );
  end

Also, you will want to add run these commands when using MATLAByrinth on ACISS:
  module purge
  module load python/2.7.2 
  module load numpy/1.6.1 
  module load mpi-tor/openmpi-1.4.5_gcc-4.4.6 
  module load matlab/r2011b

3) Refer to the MATLAByrinth README file to see how to test the installation.

